{
  "__inputs": [],
  "__requires": [],
  "annotations": { "list": [] },
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "panels": [
    {
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "## ⚠️ Pub/Sub Metrics Not Yet Available\n\nThe **Pub/Sub Emulator** (`gcr.io/google.com/cloudsdktool/cloud-sdk`) does not expose Prometheus metrics.\nFor local development, worker-side counters (below) serve as a proxy for queue health.\n\n**For production (GCP):** Use the [GCP Pub/Sub Stackdriver exporter](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/stackdriver-prometheus-sidecar) or [pubsub_exporter](https://github.com/binxio/pubsub-exporter) to scrape `pubsub.googleapis.com/subscription/num_undelivered_messages` and expose it to Prometheus.\n\n**Worker-side proxy metrics available now:**\n- `orders_accepted_total` (API) vs `orders_completed_total + orders_failed_total` (Worker) → approximates queue depth\n- `worker_redeliveries_total` → indicates NACKed messages still in queue\n- `order_e2e_latency_seconds` → latency grows as queue backs up",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Setup Required for Full Queue Visibility",
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
          "custom": { "lineWidth": 2 },
          "unit": "short",
          "min": 0
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": { "id": "byName", "options": "Queue Depth (approx)" },
            "properties": [
              { "id": "color", "value": { "fixedColor": "orange", "mode": "fixed" } },
              { "id": "custom.lineWidth", "value": 3 }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 5 },
      "id": 2,
      "options": { "legend": { "calcs": ["mean", "max", "last"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" }, "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" } },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "(sum(increase(orders_accepted_total{job=\"api\"}[2m])) or vector(0)) - (sum(increase(orders_completed_total{job=\"worker\"}[2m])) or vector(0)) - (sum(increase(orders_failed_total{job=\"worker\"}[2m])) or vector(0))",
          "legendFormat": "Queue Depth (approx, 2m window)",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(orders_accepted_total{job=\"api\"}[1m]))",
          "legendFormat": "Enqueue Rate (accepted / s)",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "(sum(rate(orders_completed_total{job=\"worker\"}[1m])) or vector(0)) + (sum(rate(orders_failed_total{job=\"worker\"}[1m])) or vector(0))",
          "legendFormat": "Dequeue Rate (completed+failed / s)",
          "refId": "C"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Queue Depth & Processing Rate (Worker-Side Proxy)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
          "custom": { "lineWidth": 2 },
          "unit": "ops"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 13 },
      "id": 3,
      "options": { "legend": { "calcs": ["mean", "max"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" }, "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" } },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(orders_accepted_total{job=\"api\"}[1m]))",
          "legendFormat": "Publish Rate (API accepted)",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "(sum(rate(orders_completed_total{job=\"worker\"}[1m])) or vector(0)) + (sum(rate(orders_failed_total{job=\"worker\"}[1m])) or vector(0))",
          "legendFormat": "Consumer Rate (Worker finished)",
          "refId": "B"
        },
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(worker_redeliveries_total{job=\"worker\"}[1m])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "Redelivery Rate (NACK backlog)",
          "refId": "C"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Publish vs. Consumer Rate",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${datasource}" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": { "mode": "palette-classic" },
          "custom": { "lineWidth": 2 },
          "unit": "s"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 13 },
      "id": 4,
      "options": { "legend": { "calcs": ["mean", "max"], "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom" }, "tooltip": { "mode": "multi" } },
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(order_e2e_latency_seconds_bucket{job=\"worker\"}[1m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p95 E2E Latency (queue pressure indicator)",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (le) (rate(order_e2e_latency_seconds_bucket{job=\"worker\"}[1m])))",
          "legendFormat": "p99 E2E Latency",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "E2E Latency as Queue Pressure Indicator",
      "description": "Rising p95/p99 latency indicates queue backup. Correlated with Queue Depth panel above.",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "gridPos": { "h": 4, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 21 },
      "id": 5,
      "options": {
        "content": "### 📌 Production Queue Depth (GCP Pub/Sub)\nOnce connected to real GCP, add this PromQL (requires Stackdriver exporter):\n```\npubsub_subscription_num_undelivered_messages{subscription_id=\"buy-ticket-sub\"}\npubsub_subscription_oldest_unacked_message_age{subscription_id=\"buy-ticket-sub\"}\n```",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Production Metrics Reference",
      "type": "text"
    }
  ],
  "refresh": "10s",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
